<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BRAKE BOOSTER AND MASTER CYLINDER - TROUBLESHOOTING - PEDAL CONDITIONS - PEDAL TRAVEL,
        PEDAL POSITION AND PEDAL EFFORT ISSUES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>PEDAL CONDITIONS - PEDAL TRAVEL, PEDAL POSITION AND PEDAL EFFORT ISSUES</title>
        <table id="t0401702" tblwidth="full-page">
            <title>Troubleshooting Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="s1t3"/>
                <thead>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">CONDITION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">POSSIBLE CAUSE</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">CORRECTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="2">
                            <para>Increase in brake pedal travel.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Air in brake lines or master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Bleed brake system. Determine air entry point and repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. External brake fluid leak.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Tighten outlet port brake line nuts at master cylinder. Refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s04017y_X0401706.xml" xrefid="x0401706">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>. Replace
                                brake lines or master cylinder, if required. Check all components and connections in the
                                brake fluid system for leaks, repair or replace as needed.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Internal brake fluid leak.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Replace master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="1">
                            <para>Brake pedal goes to floor under continuous force.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. External brake fluid leak.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Tighten outlet port brake line nuts at master cylinder. Refer to
                                <hotlnk document="s04017y_X0401706.xml" xrefid="x0401706">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>. Replace
                                brake lines or master cylinder, if required. Check all components and connections in the
                                brake fluid system for leaks, repair or replace as needed.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Internal leaks in master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Replace master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Brake pedal goes to floor on first application, OK on subsequent applications.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Pad and piston knockback caused by loose wheel bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Adjust, tighten or replace faulty parts as needed.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Brake pedal drops when engine starts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Flow rate from power steering pump is too high.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Repair or replace power steering pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="3">
                            <para>Brake pedal does not return, when power steering fluid is at operating temperature of
                                at least 125 degrees.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Brake pedal linkage binding (possibly because pedal too far to the right or left of
                                the Hydro-Max&#8482; booster center).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Center brake pedal on Hydro-Max&#8482; booster, replace pedal, pedal bushings or
                                pedal pin, if necessary.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Flow rate from power steering pump is too high.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Repair or replace power steering pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Malfunctioning Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Replace Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Malfunctioning master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>4. Replace master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="2">
                            <para>Springy or spongy brake pedal.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Air in brake fluid system.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Bleed brakes.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Brake fluid has absorbed water or other contaminants (low boiling point).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Drain, clean brake fluid system, replace brake fluid with approved brake fluid.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Weak brake hoses that expand under pressure.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Replace hoses.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="3">
                            <para>Brake pedal pulsations.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Parking brake valve (HR1) frequently interrupting power steering flow through
                                Hydro-Max&#8482; booster (only applies to vehicle with a hydraulic parking brake HR1
                                parking valve).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Replace HR1 parking valve.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Loose, worn or damaged front wheel bearings.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Adjust, tighten or replace faulty parts as needed.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Excessive variation in rotor thickness.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Resurface or replace rotors.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Excessive lateral runout in rotors.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>4. Resurface or replace rotors.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>High brake pedal force required to stop vehicle with engine running.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Pedal linkage binding.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Remove source of binding. Pedal should be centered with Hydro-Max&#8482; booster,
                                and pedal rod angle should be no lower than 5 degrees from center line of Hydro-Max&#8482;
                                booster. Replace pedal, pedal bushings or pedal pin, if necessary.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Malfunctioning Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Replace Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Insufficient power steering flow rate or pressure capability.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Make sure power steering pump reservoir is full. Measure flow rate and pressure at
                                booster inlet, if below spec: Replace restricted tubes and hoses, tighten power steering
                                pump belt or repair or replace power steering pump, as needed.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Flow or pressure limited by the power steering gear.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>4. Repair or replace power steering gear.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5. Malfunctioning master cylinder. See note at end of Table 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>5. Replace master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6. Hydro-Max booster supply or return tubes and hoses blocked.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>6. Locate blockage, replace appropriate parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>7. Brake fluid tubes and hoses blocked.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>7. Locate blockage, replace appropriate parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>High brake pedal force required to stop vehicle with engine running (Cont).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>8. ABS HCU prevents brake fluid flow.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>8. Repair or replace HCU.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>9. Grease or brake fluid coated brake linings.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>9. Replace brake linings (as axle sets), repair cause of grease or brake fluid
                                leakage.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="6">
                            <para>High brake pedal force required to stop vehicle with engine OFF.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1. Pedal linkage binding.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1. Remove source of binding. Pedal should be centered with Hydro-Max&#8482; booster,
                                and pedal rod angle should be no lower than 5 degrees from center line of Hydro-Max&#8482;
                                booster. Replace pedal, pedal bushings or pedal pin, if necessary.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2. Malfunctioning Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2. Replace Hydro-Max&#8482; booster.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3. Malfunctioning backup pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3. Replace backup pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4. Malfunctioning master cylinder. See note at end of Table 2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>4. Replace master cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5. Brake fluid tubes and hoses blocked.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>5. Locate blockage, replace appropriate parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6. ABS HCU prevents brake fluid flow.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>6. Repair or replace HCU.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>-</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>7. Grease or brake fluid coated brake linings.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>7. Replace brake linings (as axle sets), repair cause of grease or brake fluid
                                leakage.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="s1t3">
                            <note>
                                <para>A common cause of a malfunctioning master cylinder is swollen seals due to putting
                                    the wrong fluid (usually power steering fluid) into the master cylinder. This is
                                    easily detectable. The diaphragms inside the fill caps of the reservoir will be
                                    swollen. If the diaphragms are swollen, the master cylinder must be replaced. Also,
                                    the calipers must be examined for swollen seals. If the caliper seals are swollen,
                                    the calipers must be repaired or replaced. Also, the brake hoses may be damaged and
                                    weakened. They should be replaced. Finally, the brake lines should be flushed with
                                    clean brake fluid until clean brake fluid comes through each of the bleeder screws
                                    at the calipers.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
